      "message": "The interface here and in ansiblebot don\u0027t really abstract out anything, they seem to primary placeholders to make testing easier. \nThat\u0027s a valid use case, but they should still serve the purpose of an interface and \nabstract away device details. \n\nIMO it\u0027s time to structure this differently, i.e. \n- have a package devices that define interfaces for devices and (maybe) device groups\n- have a package for each device type we have: edgeswitch, arduino, mpower, ansible?\n  This should also support to instantiate devices from a config file \n- have command line programs like powercycle, consensustaker that use the device interface",
